message.text:
How do you celebrate for the Autumn's arrival?

 For Japanese, and many Asian countries, one of the most popular events in fall is to enjoy the moonlight, "Otsuki-mi(おつきみ)."
 In Japan, it is a tradition to enjoy the harvest moon(仲秋の名月、ちゅうしゅうのめいげつ), putting Japanese pampas grass(すすき) aside and having tasty moon-veiwing dumplings(お月見団子、おつきみだんご).

 Usually, we prefer decorating the dumplings with grass which is not colorful, not with pretty flowers, because it can make the moonlight more beautiful. 
This preference may let you feel "Wabi-sabi," which is a Japanese authentic perception for quiet beauty.

 When it comes to "Otsukimi," we have a tale of a rabit pounding mochi on the moon, and you may find the silhouette of the rabit in the moon. Depending on countries and cultures, the figure in the moon seems different; some say it is like a donkey and others say it looks like a crab! 

Do you have any tales about the moon in your culture??

 秋の風物詩といえば「お月見」。
 ススキを飾ってお月見団子を食べながら、「仲秋の名月」を楽しむのが慣わしです。「お月見」の時期になると、夏の暑さも落ち着いて、秋の涼しさを感じる季節になります。華やかなお花ではなく、すすきを飾るあたりも、日本の「わび・さび」の風流なのかもしれません。

 ところで、日本では、月でウサギが餅つきをしているという逸話があり、月の模様もウサギの餅つきの様子を表していると言われています。世界の各国では、月の模様がカニやロバなどに見えると言われているそうですが、皆さんの国には月にまつわるどのような逸話がありますか？

 http://words.marugotoweb.jp/search_detail.php?id=1729&p=1&q=つき&source=search&lang=en

message.text:
#Hiragana Master
 Say it Together! Basic Japanese Words in Japanese Alphabetical Order.
 Today's Word is "Na" NATTO（fermented soybeans)　#nihongo　
 日本の単語を五十音順にわかりやすく紹介！「な」っとう


 Tasty and healthy, NATTO（納豆） is one of the most common foods served for breakfast in Japan. Of course, it can be eaten for lunch and dinner, even for a light snack if you love it! When you hear “fermented soybeans”, you may imagine something inedible, and yes indeed, the smell is quite strong. But hey, fermented food is all around! Just like cheese!
 There are many Japanese food made of soybeans, such as “とうふ(tofu)”, and “しょうゆ(soy-sauce)”.
 If you get a chance, try it!

 おいしくて健康的な納豆は、日本で朝食としてよく食卓に並びます。もちろん、昼食にも夕食にも出ますし、大好きならおやつにも食べられます！「発酵した大豆」と聞くと食べられない物を想像されるかもしれませんね。確かに臭いは強いですが、皆さんは日常的に発酵食品を口にしています！例えばチーズなど！
 日本食には大豆からできているものが多くあります。豆腐や醤油もその仲間です。
 もし機会があれば試してみてくださいね！

 https://www.jpf.go.jp/j/japanese/survey/tsushin/dw_pdfs/tushin34_p12-13.pdf

message.text:
<KANJI Quiz!>

 Do you know the meaning of the Kanji "仲"？ Choose the answer!
     1.desk   2. question   3. association

“仲” is made of the parts: “イ (にんべん)”representing “people” and “中” representing “between” or “inside.”
Put these together and guess the meaning!! 

Kanji may be difficult to remember for Japanese learners...
Hope you can find good tips for memorizing Kanji from our posts!

「仲」ってどういう意味か知っていますか？
漢字を覚えるのって大変ですよね。。。

http://www.anime-manga.jp/KanjiGame/School/
